r.s: Provides extra data structures and iterable/array functionality.
r.d: teds (Tentative Extra Data Structures) is a collection of data structures and iterable functionality
r.n: * Optimize Teds\Deque insert() and offsetUnset() calls with offsets when they're closer to the front of the deque than the end of the Deque. * Add Teds\strict_equals($v1, $v2): bool with stricter NAN handling than `===`. * Regenerate function arginfo with namespaced C symbols from stub.php files.
